SS2: The program will first call fork() , which creates a child process. 
After the fork, the child process prints its process ID, simulates some work by sleeping for 10 seconds, and then exits.
Meanwhile, the parent process prints its own process ID, waits for 3 seconds, and checks the child process. It sends a SIGTERM signal using kill() to terminate the child if it is still running. Finally, the parent calls wait() to collect the child's exit status, preventing the child from becoming a zombie process before the program terminates.
